    <item>
      <title>12/24/2008 - Libertarianism Explained</title>
      <pubDate>Wed, 24 Dec 2008 19:00:00 -0700</pubDate>
      <itunes:author>Nick Coons, Richard Sutton, and Jim Iannuzo</itunes:author>
      <itunes:summary>Today being Christmas Eve, tonight's program was pre-recorded.&amp;nbsp; We focus on describing the principles of libertarianism so that those new to the philosophy can understand why we oppose taxation and most laws (Hint: It's not because we want to use drugs and hoard money).&amp;nbsp; We go through the process of self-ownership, self-interest, and how our principled and pragmatic views flow from those ideas.&amp;nbsp; And as usual, we veer off on to a few tangents just to keep it interesting.&amp;nbsp; We'll be back next week on New Year's Eve with a live program.</itunes:summary>
